        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add manual provider subscription reminder foundation",
        "body": "Narrow, manual-only foundation PR for provider subscription reminders.\n\nAdds:\n- Provider-neutral manual subscription snapshot model\n- Optional local config fields for manual renewal/expiry dates\n- Separate subscription menu line formatting (not quota/reset)\n- Dedupeable reminder timing logic (30/7/3/1 days, today, expired)\n- Focused tests\n\nLatest-head proof:\n- Head SHA: `995a0411316ac6e5316ca02005eeb5d2ce83671f`\n- CI: green on latest head (`lint-build-test`, both `build-linux-cli` jobs, GitGuardian)\n- Parser blocker fixed: `updatedAt` now preserves ISO-8601 instants.\n- Renewal/expiry behavior unchanged: manual/date-only parsing remains scoped to `subscriptionRenewsAt` and `subscriptionExpiresAt`.\n- Regression coverage added for `updatedAt = \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"` decoding to the exact ISO-8601 instant.\n\nLocal app validation:\n- Built and launched the debug app bundle from latest head with an isolated local config.\n- Save/persistence: the app wrote the manual `subscriptionSnapshot` back to the isolated config.\n- Relaunch persistence: after relaunch, `updatedAt` persisted as `2026-05-24T00:00:00.000Z`.\n- Menu row: verified the debug bundle exposes a CodexBar status item and opens the menu.\n- Notification path: with a one-day renewal date in the isolated config, the app wrote `fired: [\"renewsIn1Day\"]`, confirming the reminder trigger path.\n- Clear path: remains the same scoped settings-store path (`setProviderSubscriptionSnapshot(..., nil)`) covered by focused tests; not re-run through live UI to avoid exposing local account data.\n\nDoes not add:\n- Billing-page scraping, cookie/session reads, or billing endpoint calls\n- Any diagnostic export changes\n- Any raw account/billing identifiers or raw provider payload storage\n\nPrivacy:\n- Local-only validation\n- No provider scraping\n- No cookie/session reads\n- No billing endpoint calls\n- No raw account or billing identifiers stored in the isolated config\n",
